The Telegraph's Matt Law writes: &quot;Chelsea have made it clear to Southampton they remain interested in signing &pound;60m-rated Van Dijk, but have also agreed to respect the stance of the St Mary&rsquo;s club until any point that it changes.<br />
<br />
&quot;It is hoped that by taking a soft approach that Chelsea will put themselves first in line to potentially land Van Dijk if and when Southampton&rsquo;s stance changes, whether that is before the end of this window, in January or even next summer.&quot;
